## What to do

Add a `--work-scope-cel` flag to both `activity create` and `activity edit` commands. This flag takes comma-separated label keys and stores a structured `workScopeCel` record on the activity.

### 1. cmd/root.go â€” Add flags (2 places)

In the `activity create` command flags array (around line 169), add after the existing `work-scope` flag:
```go
&cli.StringFlag{Name: "work-scope-cel", Usage: "CEL work scope labels (comma-separated, e.g. open-source,cli-development)"},
```

In the `activity edit` command flags array (around line 182), add after the existing `work-scope` flag:
```go
&cli.StringFlag{Name: "work-scope-cel", Usage: "CEL work scope labels (comma-separated)"},
```

### 2. cmd/activity.go â€” Add a helper function

Add this helper function (e.g. near the top, after imports):
```go
// buildWorkScopeCel parses comma-separated label keys and builds a workScopeCel record.
// Labels are trimmed and deduplicated. The CEL expression is auto-generated as scope.hasAll([...]).
func buildWorkScopeCel(csv string) (map[string]any, error) {
	parts := strings.Split(csv, ",")
	seen := make(map[string]bool)
	var labels []string
	for _, p := range parts {
		key := strings.TrimSpace(p)
		if key == "" {
			continue
		}
		if !keyPattern.MatchString(key) {
			return nil, fmt.Errorf("invalid label key %q: must be lowercase letters/numbers separated by hyphens", key)
		}
		if !seen[key] {
			seen[key] = true
			labels = append(labels, key)
		}
	}
	if len(labels) == 0 {
		return nil, fmt.Errorf("at least one label is required for --work-scope-cel")
	}

	// Build CEL expression
	var expr string
	if len(labels) == 1 {
		expr = fmt.Sprintf("scope.has(%q)", labels[0])
	} else {
		quoted := make([]string, len(labels))
		for i, l := range labels {
			quoted[i] = fmt.Sprintf("%s", l)
		}
		expr = fmt.Sprintf("scope.hasAll([%s])", strings.Join(quoted, ", "))
	}

	return map[string]any{
		"$type":      atproto.CollectionActivity + "#workScopeCel",
		"expression": expr,
		"labels":     labels,
		"version":    "v1",
	}, nil
}
```

NOTE: `keyPattern` is already defined in `cmd/workscope.go` (same package) as `var keyPattern = regexp.MustCompile("^[a-z0-9]+(-[a-z0-9]+)*$")`. It is accessible from `cmd/activity.go` since they share the `cmd` package.

